          <rt-link slot="name" href="https://www.rottentomatoes.com/critic/guardian-staff">
            Guardian Staff
          </rt-link>
          <rt-text slot="publication" size="0.875">
            Guardian
          </rt-text>
          <span slot="timestamp">04/10/2020</span>
          <div slot="rating">
            <score-icon-critics size="1.5" sentiment="POSITIVE"></score-icon-critics>
            <span></span>
          </div>
          
            <span slot="review">The western cinema has needed for a long time its own kind of healthy puritanism to counter that from the east - notably Poland - and with directors like Fellini and Karel Reisz it now seems that it is getting it.</span>
            <rt-link slot="review-link" context="link" href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/apr/10/la-dolce-vita-defies-all-the-ballyhoo-fellini-1961" target="_blank">
              Go to Full Review
            </rt-link>
          
          <rt-button
            slot="options-menu"
            theme="transparent"
            data-MediaCriticsReviewsManager="optionsMenuBtn:click"
            data-encrypted-publication-id="J4yzkxZP"
          ><rt-icon icon="more"></rt-icon></rt-button>
        </review-card-critic>
      
        <review-card-critic
          slot="tile"
          fixed-size
          
          approved-publication
          
          top-publication
        >
          <rt-link slot="avatar-icon" href="https://www.rottentomatoes.com/critic/eric-rhode">
            
              <avatar-icon display-name="Eric Rhode" initials="ER"></avatar-icon>
            
          </rt-link>
          <rt-link slot="name" href="https://www.rottentomatoes.com/critic/eric-rhode">
            Eric Rhode
          </rt-link>
          <rt-text slot="publication" size="0.875">
            Sight &amp; Sound
          </rt-text>
          <span slot="timestamp">02/10/2020</span>
          <div slot="rating">
            <score-icon-critics size="1.5" sentiment="NEGATIVE"></score-icon-critics>
            <span></span>
          </div>
          
            <span slot="review">Fellini admits to having a confused sense of values, to being as uncertain as a child. Why then does he try to make realist films? It&#39;s a great pity; for if La Dolce Vita had beenless grandiose and more private and personal it might have worked.</span>
            <rt-link slot="review-link" context="link" href="https://archive.org/details/Sight_and_Sound_1961_01_BFI_GB/page/n51" target="_blank">
              Go to Full Review
            </rt-link>
          
          <rt-button
            slot="options-menu"
